<integerCodeSet xmlns="http://www.energistics.org/energyml/data/uomv1" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.energistics.org/energyml/data/uomv1 EnergisticsUnitOfMeasureDictionary_V1.0.xsd" version="1.0">
	<title>Energistics Integer Code V1.0</title>
	<originator>Energistics</originator>
	<description>This specification assigns an integer code to Quantity Classes and to selected Units of Measure. 
		The data is intended to be used in binary formats which constrain the space available for defining 
		class and unit information. 
		The data contains references to the Energistics Unit of Measure Dictionary V1.0 specification. 
		A code may be deprecated but will never be removed. 
		However, only "base for conversion" unit symbols are assigned a code and the conversion base is 
		constrained to SI symbols so unit changes should be rare. 
		If new classes are added in the associated specification then new codes will be added to the Code 
		specification. 
		The associated class dictionary will assert the unit symbol of the conversion base for each class. 
		That is, this specification merely maps codes to the semantics defined in the associated dictionary. 
		If there are multiple quantity classes with the same dimension then only the (numerically 
		equivalent) alternative base for a class might be represented. 
		This data is distributed under the Energistics License Agreement at http://www.energistics.org. 
		Use of this file constitutes agreement with the Energistics License Agreement. 
		Copyright (c) 2014 Energistics. 
		All rights reserved.
	</description>
